    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - FUEL SYSTEM - Fuel Filter and
        Piping
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Fuel Filter and Piping</title>
        <svcproc graphiccount="4">
            <title>Removal</title>
            <figure id="f1201203" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg3/EG3292.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Fuel Filter Lever Locations</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Filter Assembly</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Filter Shut Off Lever, CLOSED Position</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Filter Shut Off Lever, DRAIN Position</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove all the hose connections attached to the fuel filter/pressure regulating valve
                    assembly as follows:
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Place a suitable container at the end of the fuel drain hose in order to catch the
                        draining fuel.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Move the fuel filter drain lever to the DRAIN position.</para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1201204" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg3/EG3293.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Removing Hoses from the Regulating Valve</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Pressure Regulating Valve</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Hoses</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>On earlier model engines with non-split shot fuel systems, the two fuel hoses are for fuel
                        return from the cylinder heads. On later model engines with split shot fuel systems, the two
                        fuel hoses are for fuel supply from the pump to the regulating valve.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two fuel filter hoses from the fuel filter pressure regulating valve. Cap the
                    fittings on the cylinder head.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the bolts that secure the fuel pressure regulating valve to the fuel filter.
                    Check for damage or corrosion.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1201205" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg3/EG3282.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Removing the Fuel Tubes</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Filter Lid</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Supply to Fuel Transfer Pump</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">fuel transfer Pump to Fuel Filter</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Filter to Fuel Transfer Pump</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Tie Strap or Retaining Clamp</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Drain</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the tie strap or retaining clamp from the fuel tubes.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen the hose clamps and remove the four fuel tubes.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1201207" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg3/EG3294.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Removing the Fuel Filter Tower</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Filter and Support Bracket</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Stud Nuts (4)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the four stud nuts that secure the fuel filter tower to the cylinder head. Remove
                    the fuel filter tower.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
